CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 15, 1954, pg. 34 reads: " Salvation Army Drive Workers - Workers in Salvation Army drive met Friday evening at 809 Bryn Mawr Road, home of Mrs. Eunice Cook, director of the fundraising effort in the Hill District. Seated, left to right, are Mmes, James A. Greenlee, Lucille Hayes, Eunice W. Cook, Elizabeth Hopson and Nannie G. Moone.  Standing: Hellen Hall, Marie T. Tabb, Harriet McDonald and Beatrice Wills. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nine women including seated left to right, Mrs. James A. Greenlee, Lucille Hayes, Eunice W. Cook, Elizabeth Hopson and Nannie G. Moone, standing left to right, Helen Hall, Marie T. Tabb, Harriet McDonald and Beatrice Wills, gathered around table in Eunice Cook's home at 809 Bryn Mawr Road
